Nice obfuscated Javascript.  It loads engine1327548.js, which does not-much-more than:<p><pre><code>    google_searches = string((secsToday) * 35112);
</code></pre>
Flagged as spam.<p>I really loved their add-one-and-URI-escape-each-character encryption though.  That took 1 line of Perl to decode!  I had to uri-unescape, and then subtract 1!<p>Edit: full source and the decoder, for those that care: <a href="http://gist.github.com/326637#file_engine1327548.js" rel="nofollow">http://gist.github.com/326637#file_engine1327548.js</a><p>Sorry, but trying to hide code you want the user to execute just amuses me.  Lots of nice copy-pasta in there.
